%20that%20individuals%20in%20similar%20situations--such%20as%20those%20with%20tax%20payment%20issues%20due%20to%20addiction--typically%20receive%20non-criminal%20resolutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20contended%20that%20Hunter's%20case%20was%20treated%20differently%2C%20leading%20to%20felony%20charges%20despite%20the%20absence%20of%20aggravating%20factors.%20Biden%20also%20stressed%20his%20commitment%20to%20not%20interfere%20with%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20decision-making%2C%20despite%20his%20belief%20that%20his%20son%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bselectively%20and%20unfairly%20prosecuted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20I%20signed%20a%20pardon%20for%20my%20son%20Hunter.%20From%20the%20day%20I%20took%20office%2C%20I%20said%20I%20would%20not%20interfere%20with%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20decision-making%2C%20and%20I%20kept%20my%20word%20even%20as%20I%20have%20watched%20my%20son%20being%20selectively%20and%20unfairly%20prosecuted.%20Without%20aggravating%20factors%20like%20use%20in%20a%20crime%2C%20multiple%20purchases%2C%20or%20buying%20a%20weapon%20as%20a%20straw%20purchaser%2C%20people%20are%20almost%20never%20brought%20to%20trial%20on%20felony%20charges%20solely%20for%20how%20they%20filled%20out%20a%20gun%20form.%20Those%20who%20were%20late%20paying%20their%20taxes%20because%20of%20serious%20addictions%20but%20paid%20them%20back%20subsequently%20with%20interest%20and%20penalties%20are%20typically%20given%20non-criminal%20resolutions.%20It%20is%20clear%20that%20Hunter%20was%20treated%20differently%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20explained%20that%20the%20charges%20against%20his%20son%20were%20initiated%20after%20political%20opponents%20in%20Congress%20pushed%20for%20the%20case%20to%20be%20brought%20forward.%20He%20added%20that%20a%20plea%20deal%2C%20which%20had%20been%20negotiated%20with%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%2C%20unravelled%20in%20court%20due%20to%20political%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26q